[Patient] What foods should I eat to manage my heart failure? 
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins. Limit sodium and watch portion sizes. 
[Patient] How can I find healthy food in my unsafe neighborhood? 
[Educator] Consider online grocery delivery or community-supported agriculture programs for fresh produce. 
[Patient] Are there any budget-friendly options for heart-healthy foods? 
[Educator] Look for sales, buy in bulk, and plan meals ahead to save money on nutritious ingredients. 
[Patient] Can you recommend easy recipes for heart-healthy meals? 
[Educator] Try simple dishes like grilled chicken with veggies or a quinoa salad for tasty heart-healthy options. 
[Patient] How can I make sure I'm eating the right foods for my heart? 
[Educator] Read nutrition labels, cook at home, and seek guidance from healthcare providers or dietitians.